<text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <p xml:id="Aink150-kilavi">
        muṉṉorukāṟ pirintuvanta talaimakaṉ piṉṉum pirintuvantuḻi avaṉai muyaṅkāḷāka, tōḻi, nī ivvāṟu ceytaṟkukkāraṇam eṉ eṉṟu viṉaviyavaḻit talaimakaḷ tōḻikkut talaimakaṉ kēṭpac colliyatu. </p>    <p xml:lang="en">
        Spoken by the heroine - as the hero was listening - to the confidante, the confidante having asked, ‘What is the reason for you behaving this way?’, - [the heroine] being one who did not embrace him when he came [back] after having separated [from her] again/afterwords, [that] hero who [already] came, having separated once previously.
  </p>
 </div>      
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="Aink150">
<l>ekkar ñāḻa naṟumalarp peruñciṉaip</l>
<l>puṇari tiḷaikkun tuṟaivaṉ</l>
<l>puṇarvi ṉiṉṉā ṉarumpuṇar viṉaṉē</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
        <l>The man from the ghat where the ocean bubbles [with]</l>
        <l>Great branches with fragrant blossoms of the Ñāḻal tree in the dunes</l>
        <l>Is not pleasing with respect to uniting. He rarely unites [with me].</l>
              </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
</text>
